1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:05,080
♪ Inside the state a city is built ♪

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:10,190
♪ Where a benevolent emperor resides ♪

3
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:15,330
♪ Court officials are brave and able ♪

4
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:22,750
♪ The empress is fair ♪

5
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:30,710
♪ Princes died too young to ascend the throne ♪

6
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:35,570
♪ Princesses are spoiled and fragile ♪

7
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:40,270
♪ Commoners are also the emperor’s children ♪

8
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:49,630
♪ All are living peacefully ♪

9
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:54,280
♪ Wish I could live a day for myself ♪

10
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,380
♪ Follow my heart and ethics without distractions ♪

11
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:03,400
♪ To be a good husband ♪

12
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,970
♪ To be a caring father ♪

13
00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:10,110
♪ We were close when we first met ♪

14
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:14,710
♪ I hope I can control my desires ♪

15
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:20,060
♪ To be a worriless emperor and father ♪

16
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,860
♪ Prudence tops all virtues ♪

17
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,480
♪ People build the state ♪

18
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:30,020
= Held in the Lonely Castle =
♪ May the world be peaceful ♪

19
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:33,020
= Episode 69 =

20
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:37,020
= Right Guard General’s Mansion =

21
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:42,020
= Gao Taotao =
Minister Han

22
00:01:42,020 --> 00:01:43,540
is still waiting outside.

23
00:01:44,740 --> 00:01:48,500
= Zhao Zongshi =

24
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:50,700
I’m too weak to get out of bed.

25
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:53,780
It’s inappropriate

26
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:56,980
to receive a minister like this.

27
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:07,220
Tell brother to apologize to His Majesty for me.

28
00:02:13,620 --> 00:02:14,300
Your Majesty,

29
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:17,180
Zongshi still refuses to lead

30
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:18,220
the Court of the Imperial Clan.

31
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:19,540
That shows

32
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:22,420
he’s humble and discreet.

33
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:24,740
It’s known to all

34
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:27,340
only a prince is qualified for that post.

35
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:29,020
Your Majesty has no son,

36
00:02:29,620 --> 00:02:30,860
so the person who takes up that post

37
00:02:31,180 --> 00:02:32,460
will be the prince

38
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,020
in line to the throne.

39
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:36,460
People are thirsty for power and wealth.

40
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:38,740
Many stoop so low

41
00:02:38,740 --> 00:02:40,140
for petty profits.

42
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:42,460
As for the throne,

43
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,500
countless men in history

44
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,660
fought for it with their lives.

45
00:02:46,620 --> 00:02:48,300
But Zongshi isn’t tempted

46
00:02:48,420 --> 00:02:49,620
but insists on giving it away.

47
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:51,540
That’s noble.

48
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,100
However,

49
00:02:54,620 --> 00:02:56,660
a state without an heir is unstable.

50
00:02:57,540 --> 00:02:59,100
Your Majesty has already selected him.

51
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:00,380
His refusal

52
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:03,460
makes him look weak.

53
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:06,340
He isn’t weak

54
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:08,940
but considerate.

55
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,700
He isn’t sure

56
00:03:11,820 --> 00:03:13,700
if I’ve decided to appoint him Crown Prince.

57
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,500
Once he takes office,

58
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:18,180
others will all assume he’s the heir,

59
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:21,580
leaving me no room to change my mind.

60
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:27,060
Your Majesty, have you...

61
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:31,100
made your decision?

62
00:03:49,580 --> 00:03:51,340
I’m officially

63
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:53,540
crowning him prince today.

64
00:03:54,940 --> 00:03:56,460
He can’t refuse it

65
00:03:57,540 --> 00:03:59,220
or he’ll be charged with disobedience.

66
00:05:27,020 --> 00:05:28,700
The Lantern Festival is approaching.

67
00:05:29,780 --> 00:05:32,620
Didn’t Huirou mention going to see lanterns?

68
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,980
She has no mood for that.

69
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:45,260
I don’t understand.

70
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:49,340
Your Majesty has convinced those censors.

71
00:05:51,380 --> 00:05:52,460
I don’t think they’ll continue

72
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:53,580
to complain about it.

73
00:05:56,340 --> 00:05:57,780
Huaiji is a eunuch.

74
00:05:58,980 --> 00:06:01,940
Huirou is unwell.

75
00:06:05,180 --> 00:06:07,180
Must Huaiji be transferred away?

76
00:06:08,620 --> 00:06:10,540
Can’t he stay with Huirou?

77
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:17,620
When she was little,

78
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,780
she loved

79
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,020
watching lanterns and games the most

80
00:06:22,060 --> 00:06:23,700
outside the palace.

81
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,020
I’ll

82
00:06:28,420 --> 00:06:29,580
take her out today.

83
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:34,260
Take her out?

84
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:38,900
But the lantern show hasn’t begun.

85
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:42,060
I’m taking her

86
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:44,220
to visit lantern makers.

87
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,660
Sir, casts of the 300 flower lanterns you ordered

88
00:07:22,940 --> 00:07:24,380
have been made.

89
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:25,660
You can have a look

90
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,260
and add other decorations

91
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,420
if you want.

92
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:31,180
This gentleman here ordered them.

93
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:32,700
He and his family are from the south

94
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,940
and happen to be in town for the Lantern Festival.

95
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:37,300
Other than watching lanterns,

96
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,220
buying some as gifts,

97
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:40,780
they’re more interested in the production process.

98
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:42,060
I see.

99
00:07:42,740 --> 00:07:43,460
Father.

100
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:45,500
This is my daughter.

101
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:46,660
Usually,

102
00:07:46,780 --> 00:07:47,860
I’m responsible for receiving clients

103
00:07:47,860 --> 00:07:48,820
and delivering materials

104
00:07:49,180 --> 00:07:50,060
while she’s at home

105
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:51,380
looking after the store.

106
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:52,860
This way, please.

107
00:07:52,860 --> 00:07:53,780
- Please. - Please come in.

108
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,340
This way, please.

109
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:57,780
Come in, please.

110
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:59,220
Feel free to look around.

111
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:00,220
You can have a look.

112
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:06,820
Those are frames.

113
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:08,620
And these

114
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:09,700
are ready to be sold.

115
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:25,500
It’s airless and noisy here.

116
00:08:26,180 --> 00:08:27,420
You’re delicate.

117
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:28,980
Why don’t you have a rest inside?

118
00:08:30,020 --> 00:08:30,740
No, thank you.

119
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:32,300
I want to see more.

120
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:34,780
Are you here the whole time?

121
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,300
This is a rush order.

122
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,580
We have to finish 300 lanterns

123
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:40,220
before the Lantern Festival

124
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:41,620
and they need to look exquisite, too,

125
00:08:41,780 --> 00:08:43,300
so we can only work day and night.

126
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:45,140
I’m sorry.

127
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:46,940
I...

128
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:48,460
- I didn’t know...
- I should thank you for the order.

129
00:08:48,460 --> 00:08:49,620
No need to apologize.

130
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:51,260
You know,

131
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,020
with your deposit,

132
00:08:53,020 --> 00:08:54,020
our whole family

133
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:55,180
can enjoy the festival.

134
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:56,500
We can’t

135
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:58,060
thank you enough.

136
00:09:00,020 --> 00:09:01,060
Let me bring you some tea.

137
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:10,140
It’s going to be dark.

138
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:11,340
You’re too little

139
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:13,100
to do such heavy work.

140
00:09:13,580 --> 00:09:14,740
It’s not heavy at all.

141
00:09:14,940 --> 00:09:16,100
This is the easiest.

142
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:18,380
I’m helping my grandmother wash the silk

143
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:19,500
and helping my sister move it.

144
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:20,620
After I finish,

145
00:09:20,780 --> 00:09:21,900
I can go see Emperor,

146
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:23,820
Empress and Princess

147
00:09:23,820 --> 00:09:25,580
at the Lantern Festival.

148
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:28,940
See Emperor,

149
00:09:28,940 --> 00:09:30,340
Empress and Princess at the Lantern Festival?

150
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:33,860
There are lantern shows and games.

151
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,460
They’re nothing.

152
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:38,220
I want to see Emperor, Empress and Princess.

153
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:39,700
Why?

154
00:09:40,180 --> 00:09:41,340
Because they’re Emperor

155
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:42,820
Empress and Princess.

156
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,140
Father,

157
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:25,980
you weren’t taking me to see lanterns

158
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:29,780
but the people

159
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:31,340
Sima Guang described.

160
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:38,060
You want me to continue to be a Buddha

161
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:39,180
they worship,

162
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:41,700
don’t you?

163
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:49,500
I’m a Buddha in their eyes

164
00:10:50,420 --> 00:10:51,740
and a puppet in officials’ hands.

165
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:55,460
Or you’d rather I hand over

166
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,060
the strings to them

167
00:10:58,620 --> 00:10:59,740
so that they can manipulate me

168
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:03,460
and pose me as the ideal role model,

169
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:06,740
correct?

170
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:15,620
Huirou,

171
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:19,460
I want you to know

172
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:22,620
that I hate

173
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:25,940
to just be a statue

174
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:28,180
to be bowed,

175
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,020
given offerings

176
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:31,500
and be held in awe and fear by people.

177
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:34,300
I hope

178
00:11:36,380 --> 00:11:38,140
we can be

179
00:11:39,260 --> 00:11:40,660
their sun in the morning,

180
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:42,820
stars at night,

181
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:45,820
and the light

182
00:11:45,820 --> 00:11:47,500
they can see whenever they look up

183
00:11:47,780 --> 00:11:50,420
after working painstakingly.

184
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:55,700
So I’m willing

185
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:58,700
to be a kite with the string in officials’ hands

186
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,940
that they can admire, follow

187
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:05,020
and adjust the direction cautiously.

188
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:07,980
The higher it flies,

189
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:09,580
the easier it goes astray,

190
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:14,180
so it needs to be watched by people on the ground

191
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:16,300
to ensure its safety.

192
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:21,780
Their sun in the morning,

193
00:12:24,460 --> 00:12:25,700
stars at night?

194
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:30,780
But...

195
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:33,820
But Sima Guang is too stubborn...

196
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:34,860
Huirou,

197
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:37,460
the strong-willed

198
00:12:37,460 --> 00:12:39,220
are always stubborn.

199
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:42,540
Sima Guang is talented

200
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:43,820
but he never acts willfully.

201
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:46,500
He’s honest and upright, self-disciplined,

202
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:48,940
responsible and caring.

203
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:53,020
He cares about the masses,

204
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:55,580
so he’s hypercritical of you, of us.

205
00:12:57,620 --> 00:12:59,620
He witnessed how much people suffered.

206
00:13:00,060 --> 00:13:01,340
Their lives are more painful than yours

207
00:13:01,620 --> 00:13:03,580
or mine,

208
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,100
such as the girl you just saw,

209
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:11,820
those old women who were washing silk

210
00:13:12,180 --> 00:13:13,300
and those who were coloring lanterns.

211
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:16,940
Actually, Yuanheng,

212
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:19,940
I mean Huaiji,

213
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:23,220
his mother and grandmother

214
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:24,940
were just like them.

215
00:13:27,860 --> 00:13:31,100
Huirou, Sima Guang isn’t merciless.

216
00:13:31,460 --> 00:13:32,420
If he were,

217
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,740
he wouldn’t have abandoned

218
00:13:34,740 --> 00:13:36,140
the idea of killing him

219
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:37,860
after knowing

220
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:39,980
Huaiji’s background.

221
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:43,740
Huaiji...

222
00:13:45,980 --> 00:13:46,780
Father,

223
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,020
if I had a choice,

224
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:52,020
I’d rather

225
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:54,020
work as hard as them

226
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,100
every day

227
00:13:56,620 --> 00:13:59,020
as long as I could be with Huaiji.

228
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:02,340
No one

229
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,940
can choose his or her fate.

230
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,700
Even if

231
00:14:08,780 --> 00:14:10,220
I let you

232
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:12,140
become one of them,

233
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:13,260
Huirou,

234
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,780
could you really endure

235
00:14:15,780 --> 00:14:17,100
such heavy labor?

236
00:14:19,020 --> 00:14:20,460
You’ve been a princess

237
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:23,380
since you were born

238
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,980
and you can only live as one

239
00:14:26,420 --> 00:14:27,540
just like me

240
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:30,620
who can only be an emperor.

241
00:14:44,140 --> 00:14:45,220
It’s my fault.

242
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:50,420
I shouldn’t have only told you to read

243
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:52,020
well-composed poems

244
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:54,860
and paint flowers and birds

245
00:14:56,380 --> 00:14:57,820
or spoiled you so much

246
00:14:58,860 --> 00:15:01,460
and stopped you from taking your responsibility.

247
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:04,900
You should’ve read Bai Juyi’s poem,

248
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:08,700
“Coal seller in a thin robe

249
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:13,220
prays for a cold weather
to sell his coal at a high price”

250
00:15:15,060 --> 00:15:17,020
and Fan Zhongyan’s verse,

251
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:20,700
“The little fish boat has to ride the waves”.

252
00:15:23,580 --> 00:15:25,140
Like them, Sima Guang

253
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:27,940
has compassion

254
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:29,540
for those poor people.

255
00:15:31,020 --> 00:15:31,980
He is, as a matter of fact,

256
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:34,620
way too stubborn.

257
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:38,340
But think about it,

258
00:15:39,860 --> 00:15:41,860
hadn’t you been too willful

259
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:43,260
and indulged by me,

260
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:46,020
Sima Guang wouldn’t have acted like that.

261
00:15:47,620 --> 00:15:49,460
If you’re still unwilling to change,

262
00:15:50,180 --> 00:15:51,060
Sima Guang

263
00:15:51,780 --> 00:15:53,620
is likely to become stubborn again.

264
00:15:55,940 --> 00:15:57,380
Even without him,

265
00:15:57,780 --> 00:15:59,260
there are other officials.

266
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:01,700
Those who won’t give up

267
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:03,220
their stubbornness for the greater good

268
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:05,860
are the backbone of our nation.

269
00:16:08,820 --> 00:16:09,860
I won’t meet

270
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:11,300
their unreasonable demand

271
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:12,980
to harm the innocent Huaiji

272
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:15,540
but I won’t allow your willfulness

273
00:16:15,980 --> 00:16:17,780
to keep fueling their stubbornness, either.

274
00:16:19,460 --> 00:16:21,820
It’s bad for the state

275
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:23,580
and you

276
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:28,220
because I can’t protect you forever.

277
00:16:34,380 --> 00:16:35,260
Right now,

278
00:16:37,540 --> 00:16:38,780
I won’t do anything

279
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:40,500
to Huaiji,

280
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:43,940
but if you insist on keeping him with you,

281
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:48,060
then he’ll no longer

282
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:50,100
be one of the toiling masses

283
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,700
in others’ eyes

284
00:16:53,580 --> 00:16:55,780
but an evil eunuch who seduces princess.

285
00:16:57,420 --> 00:16:58,300
You...

286
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:02,220
really think you can shield him?

287
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:22,220
Father,

288
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:27,620
let Huaiji go.

289
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:33,140
That’s my only request.

290
